Brandes Investment Trust - Brandes Institutional Enhanced Income Fund: Private Company Information - Bloomberg









































  





















































































July 26, 2017 1:52 PM ET
Capital Markets

Company Overview of Brandes Investment Trust - Brandes Institutional Enhanced Income Fund



Snapshot People




Company Overview
As of December 29, 2009, Brandes Investment Trust - Brandes Institutional Enhanced Income Fund has gone out of business. Brandes Investment Trust - Brandes Institutional Enhanced Income Fund is an open ended balanced mutual fund launched and managed by Brandes Investment Partners, L.P. The fund invests in the public equity and fixed income markets across the globe. It invests in stocks and bonds of companies operating across diversified sectors. The fund invests in value stocks of top 250 companies worldwide, based on their market caps. It invests in fixed income securities including debt securities issued by U.S. and foreign companies, debt obligations issued or guaranteed by the U.S. Gover...
As of December 29, 2009, Brandes Investment Trust - Brandes Institutional Enhanced Income Fund has gone out of business. Brandes Investment Trust - Brandes Institutional Enhanced Income Fund is an open ended balanced mutual fund launched and managed by Brandes Investment Partners, L.P. The fund invests in the public equity and fixed income markets across the globe. It invests in stocks and bonds of companies operating across diversified sectors. The fund invests in value stocks of top 250 companies worldwide, based on their market caps. It invests in fixed income securities including debt securities issued by U.S. and foreign companies, debt obligations issued or guaranteed by the U.S. Government and foreign governments, U.S. and foreign mortgage-backed securities, collateralized mortgage obligations, and asset-backed debt securities. The fund invests in investment-grade debt securities and non-investment grade debt securities rated at least BBB- (or its equivalent) by one or more of Moody's, Standard & Poor's, or Fitch. It employs fundamental analysis while creating its portfolio. The fund benchmarks the performance of 70% of its portfolio against the Barclays Capital U.S. Aggregate Index and 30% against the S&P/Citigroup World $25 billion+ Index. Brandes Investment Trust - Brandes Institutional Enhanced Income Fund was formed on December 28, 2007 and is domiciled in the United States.
Detailed Description


11988 El Camino RealSuite 500San Diego, CA 92191-9048United StatesFounded in 2007



